The paper discusses compressive sensing applied to higher order tensors, which involves data representation in a particular domain and integration of data compression and acquisition. This aligns with the information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions applications such as color imaging and video sequences, which are related to computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a new framework for compressive sensing of tensors, which could fall under the signal processing (cs.SP) sub-category.
